get.summary: Get assessments with OData query capabilities
get.description:
Supports standard OData query options:
- $filter (e.g. `?$filter=CompanyId eq 123`)
- $select (e.g. `?$select=AssessmentId,Title,Status,DateModified`)
- $orderby (e.g. `?$orderby=DateCreated desc`)
- $top and $skip for paging (e.g. `?$top=25&$skip=0`)

post.summary: Import questions from an assessment template into another assessment.
post.description:
Body schema: { assessmentId: number, templateId: number, applyTo?: string }

Behavior:
- Copies all questions (and their attachments) from `templateId` into `assessmentId`.
- If `applyTo` is "server", "endpoint" or "user", questions are duplicated per matching item
  and the category is suffixed by " - {item}"; any other value creates a single copy.

requestBody.description: JSON body describing the import operation. See remarks.

post.summary: Upload an assessment Excel (.xlsx) file and import its questions into an assessment.
post.description: Accepts multipart/form-data with a JSON 'data' part and an .xlsx 'file' part, then imports questions into the specified assessment.

400.description: Validation or processing error (missing/invalid file or JSON).
